[90m15:44:06:262[0m [34m[client-request-interceptor:on][0m adding "request" event listener: async ({ request, requestId, controller }) => {
        const response = await handleRequest(
          request,
          requestId,
          this.handlersController.currentHandlers().filter(isHandlerKind("RequestHandler")),
          this.resolvedOptions,
          this.emitter,
          {
            onPassthroughResponse(request2) {
              const acceptHeader = request2.headers.get("accept");
              if (acceptHeader) {
                const nextAcceptHeader = acceptHeader.replace(
                  /(,\s+)?msw\/passthrough/,
                  ""
                );
                if (nextAcceptHeader) {
                  request2.headers.set("accept", nextAcceptHeader);
                } else {
                  request2.headers.delete("accept");
                }
              }
            }
          }
        );
        if (response) {
          controller.respondWith(response);
        }
        return;
      }

[90m15:44:06:263[0m [34m[websocket:on][0m adding "connection" event listener: async (connection) => {
    const handlers = options.getHandlers().filter(isHandlerKind("EventHandler"));
    if (handlers.length > 0) {
      options?.onMockedConnection(connection);
      await Promise.all(
        handlers.map((handler) => {
          return handler.run(connection);
        })
      );
      return;
    }
    const request = new Request(connection.client.url, {
      headers: {
        upgrade: "websocket",
        connection: "upgrade"
      }
    });
    await onUnhandledRequest(
      request,
      options.getUnhandledRequestStrategy()
    ).catch((error) => {
      const errorEvent = new Event("error");
      Object.defineProperty(errorEvent, "cause", {
        enumerable: true,
        configurable: false,
        value: error
      });
      connection.client.socket.dispatchEvent(errorEvent);
    });
    options?.onPassthroughConnection(connection);
    connection.server.connect();
  }

          request,
          requestId,
          this.handlersController.currentHandlers().filter(isHandlerKind("RequestHandler")),
          this.resolvedOptions,
          this.emitter,
          {
            onPassthroughResponse(request2) {
              const acceptHeader = request2.headers.get("accept");
              if (acceptHeader) {
                const nextAcceptHeader = acceptHeader.replace(
                  /(,\s+)?msw\/passthrough/,
                  ""
                );
                if (nextAcceptHeader) {
                  request2.headers.set("accept", nextAcceptHeader);
                } else {
                  request2.headers.delete("accept");
                }
              }
            }
          }
        );
        if (response) {
          controller.respondWith(response);
        }
        return;
      }

[90m15:44:06:305[0m [34m[websocket:on][0m adding "connection" event listener: async (connection) => {
    const handlers = options.getHandlers().filter(isHandlerKind("EventHandler"));
    if (handlers.length > 0) {
      options?.onMockedConnection(connection);
      await Promise.all(
        handlers.map((handler) => {
          return handler.run(connection);
        })
      );
      return;
    }
    const request = new Request(connection.client.url, {
      headers: {
        upgrade: "websocket",
        connection: "upgrade"
      }
    });
    await onUnhandledRequest(
      request,
      options.getUnhandledRequestStrategy()
    ).catch((error) => {
      const errorEvent = new Event("error");
      Object.defineProperty(errorEvent, "cause", {
        enumerable: true,
        configurable: false,
        value: error
      });
      connection.client.socket.dispatchEvent(errorEvent);
    });
    options?.onPassthroughConnection(connection);
    connection.server.connect();
  }

[90m15:44:06:593[0m [34m[client-request-interceptor:on][0m adding "request" event listener: async ({ request, requestId, controller }) => {
        const response = await handleRequest(
          request,
          requestId,
          this.handlersController.currentHandlers().filter(isHandlerKind("RequestHandler")),
          this.resolvedOptions,
          this.emitter,
          {
            onPassthroughResponse(request2) {
              const acceptHeader = request2.headers.get("accept");
              if (acceptHeader) {
                const nextAcceptHeader = acceptHeader.replace(
                  /(,\s+)?msw\/passthrough/,
                  ""
                );
                if (nextAcceptHeader) {
                  request2.headers.set("accept", nextAcceptHeader);
                } else {
                  request2.headers.delete("accept");
                }
              }
            }
          }
        );
        if (response) {
          controller.respondWith(response);
        }
        return;
      }

[90m15:44:06:594[0m [34m[websocket:on][0m adding "connection" event listener: async (connection) => {
    const handlers = options.getHandlers().filter(isHandlerKind("EventHandler"));
    if (handlers.length > 0) {
      options?.onMockedConnection(connection);
      await Promise.all(
        handlers.map((handler) => {
          return handler.run(connection);
        })
      );
      return;
    }
    const request = new Request(connection.client.url, {
      headers: {
        upgrade: "websocket",
        connection: "upgrade"
      }
    });
    await onUnhandledRequest(
      request,
      options.getUnhandledRequestStrategy()
    ).catch((error) => {
      const errorEvent = new Event("error");
      Object.defineProperty(errorEvent, "cause", {
        enumerable: true,
        configurable: false,
        value: error
      });
      connection.client.socket.dispatchEvent(errorEvent);
    });
    options?.onPassthroughConnection(connection);
    connection.server.connect();
  }

[90m15:44:06:833[0m [34m[websocket:on][0m adding "connection" event listener: async (connection) => {
    const handlers = options.getHandlers().filter(isHandlerKind("EventHandler"));
    if (handlers.length > 0) {
      options?.onMockedConnection(connection);
      await Promise.all(
        handlers.map((handler) => {
          return handler.run(connection);
        })
      );
      return;
    }
    const request = new Request(connection.client.url, {
      headers: {
        upgrade: "websocket",
        connection: "upgrade"
      }
    });
    await onUnhandledRequest(
      request,
      options.getUnhandledRequestStrategy()
    ).catch((error) => {
      const errorEvent = new Event("error");
      Object.defineProperty(errorEvent, "cause", {
        enumerable: true,
        configurable: false,
        value: error
      });
      connection.client.socket.dispatchEvent(errorEvent);
    });
    options?.onPassthroughConnection(connection);
    connection.server.connect();
  }

          isMockedResponse ? "response:mocked" : "response:bypass",
          {
            response,
            request,
            requestId
          }
        );
      }
[90m15:44:06:856[0m [34m[websocket:on][0m adding "connection" event listener: async (connection) => {
    const handlers = options.getHandlers().filter(isHandlerKind("EventHandler"));
    if (handlers.length > 0) {
      options?.onMockedConnection(connection);
      await Promise.all(
        handlers.map((handler) => {
          return handler.run(connection);
        })
      );
      return;
    }
    const request = new Request(connection.client.url, {
      headers: {
        upgrade: "websocket",
        connection: "upgrade"
      }
    });
    await onUnhandledRequest(
      request,
      options.getUnhandledRequestStrategy()
    ).catch((error) => {
      const errorEvent = new Event("error");
      Object.defineProperty(errorEvent, "cause", {
        enumerable: true,
        configurable: false,
        value: error
      });
      connection.client.socket.dispatchEvent(errorEvent);
    });
    options?.onPassthroughConnection(connection);
    connection.server.connect();
  }

[90m15:44:06:859[0m [34m[fetch:on][0m adding "request" event listener: async ({ request, requestId, controller }) => {
        const response = await handleRequest(
          request,
          requestId,
          this.handlersController.currentHandlers().filter(isHandlerKind("RequestHandler")),
          this.resolvedOptions,
          this.emitter,
          {
            onPassthroughResponse(request2) {
              const acceptHeader = request2.headers.get("accept");
              if (acceptHeader) {
                const nextAcceptHeader = acceptHeader.replace(
                  /(,\s+)?msw\/passthrough/,
                  ""
                );
                if (nextAcceptHeader) {
                  request2.headers.set("accept", nextAcceptHeader);
                } else {
                  request2.headers.delete("accept");
                }
              }
            }
          }
        );
        if (response) {
          controller.respondWith(response);
        }
        return;
      }

    });
    options?.onPassthroughConnection(connection);
    connection.server.connect();

[90m15:44:09:210[0m [34m[client-request-interceptor:on][0m adding "request" event listener: async ({ request, requestId, controller }) => {
        const response = await handleRequest(
          request,
          requestId,
          this.handlersController.currentHandlers().filter(isHandlerKind("RequestHandler")),
          this.resolvedOptions,
          this.emitter,
          {
            onPassthroughResponse(request2) {
              const acceptHeader = request2.headers.get("accept");
              if (acceptHeader) {
                const nextAcceptHeader = acceptHeader.replace(
                  /(,\s+)?msw\/passthrough/,
                  ""
                );
                if (nextAcceptHeader) {
                  request2.headers.set("accept", nextAcceptHeader);
                } else {
                  request2.headers.delete("accept");
                }
              }
            }
          }
        );
        if (response) {
          controller.respondWith(response);
        }
        return;
      }

[90m15:44:09:211[0m [34m[websocket:on][0m adding "connection" event listener: async (connection) => {
    const handlers = options.getHandlers().filter(isHandlerKind("EventHandler"));
    if (handlers.length > 0) {
      options?.onMockedConnection(connection);
      await Promise.all(
        handlers.map((handler) => {
          return handler.run(connection);
        })
      );
      return;
    }
    const request = new Request(connection.client.url, {
      headers: {
        upgrade: "websocket",
        connection: "upgrade"
      }
    });
    await onUnhandledRequest(
      request,
      options.getUnhandledRequestStrategy()
    ).catch((error) => {
      const errorEvent = new Event("error");
      Object.defineProperty(errorEvent, "cause", {
        enumerable: true,
        configurable: false,
        value: error
      });
      connection.client.socket.dispatchEvent(errorEvent);
    });
    options?.onPassthroughConnection(connection);
    connection.server.connect();
  }

[90m15:44:09:947[0m [34m[client-request-interceptor:on][0m adding "request" event listener: async ({ request, requestId, controller }) => {
        const response = await handleRequest(
          request,
          requestId,
          this.handlersController.currentHandlers().filter(isHandlerKind("RequestHandler")),
          this.resolvedOptions,
          this.emitter,
          {
            onPassthroughResponse(request2) {
              const acceptHeader = request2.headers.get("accept");
              if (acceptHeader) {
                const nextAcceptHeader = acceptHeader.replace(
                  /(,\s+)?msw\/passthrough/,
                  ""
                );
                if (nextAcceptHeader) {
                  request2.headers.set("accept", nextAcceptHeader);
                } else {
                  request2.headers.delete("accept");
                }
              }
            }
          }
        );
        if (response) {
          controller.respondWith(response);
        }
        return;
      }

[90m15:44:09:948[0m [34m[websocket:on][0m adding "connection" event listener: async (connection) => {
    const handlers = options.getHandlers().filter(isHandlerKind("EventHandler"));
    if (handlers.length > 0) {
      options?.onMockedConnection(connection);
      await Promise.all(
        handlers.map((handler) => {
          return handler.run(connection);
        })
      );
      return;
    }
    const request = new Request(connection.client.url, {
      headers: {
        upgrade: "websocket",
        connection: "upgrade"
      }
    });
    await onUnhandledRequest(
      request,
      options.getUnhandledRequestStrategy()
    ).catch((error) => {
      const errorEvent = new Event("error");
      Object.defineProperty(errorEvent, "cause", {
        enumerable: true,
        configurable: false,
        value: error
      });
      connection.client.socket.dispatchEvent(errorEvent);
    });
    options?.onPassthroughConnection(connection);
    connection.server.connect();
  }

[90m15:44:10:561[0m [34m[client-request-interceptor:on][0m adding "request" event listener: async ({ request, requestId, controller }) => {
        const response = await handleRequest(
          request,
          requestId,
          this.handlersController.currentHandlers().filter(isHandlerKind("RequestHandler")),
          this.resolvedOptions,
          this.emitter,
          {
            onPassthroughResponse(request2) {
              const acceptHeader = request2.headers.get("accept");
              if (acceptHeader) {
                const nextAcceptHeader = acceptHeader.replace(
                  /(,\s+)?msw\/passthrough/,
                  ""
                );
                if (nextAcceptHeader) {
                  request2.headers.set("accept", nextAcceptHeader);
                } else {
                  request2.headers.delete("accept");
                }
              }
            }
          }
        );
        if (response) {
          controller.respondWith(response);
        }
        return;
      }

[90m15:44:10:562[0m [34m[websocket:on][0m adding "connection" event listener: async (connection) => {
    const handlers = options.getHandlers().filter(isHandlerKind("EventHandler"));
    if (handlers.length > 0) {
      options?.onMockedConnection(connection);
      await Promise.all(
        handlers.map((handler) => {
          return handler.run(connection);
        })
      );
      return;
    }
    const request = new Request(connection.client.url, {
      headers: {
        upgrade: "websocket",
        connection: "upgrade"
      }
    });
    await onUnhandledRequest(
      request,
      options.getUnhandledRequestStrategy()
    ).catch((error) => {
      const errorEvent = new Event("error");
      Object.defineProperty(errorEvent, "cause", {
        enumerable: true,
        configurable: false,
        value: error
      });
      connection.client.socket.dispatchEvent(errorEvent);
    });
    options?.onPassthroughConnection(connection);
    connection.server.connect();
  }

    const handlers = options.getHandlers().filter(isHandlerKind("EventHandler"));
    if (handlers.length > 0) {
      options?.onMockedConnection(connection);
      await Promise.all(
        handlers.map((handler) => {
          return handler.run(connection);
        })
      );
      return;
    }
    const request = new Request(connection.client.url, {
      headers: {
        upgrade: "websocket",
        connection: "upgrade"
      }
    });
    await onUnhandledRequest(
      request,
      options.getUnhandledRequestStrategy()
    ).catch((error) => {
      const errorEvent = new Event("error");
      Object.defineProperty(errorEvent, "cause", {
        enumerable: true,
        configurable: false,
        value: error
      });
      connection.client.socket.dispatchEvent(errorEvent);
    });
    options?.onPassthroughConnection(connection);
    connection.server.connect();
  }

[90m15:44:12:802[0m [34m[client-request-interceptor:on][0m adding "request" event listener: async ({ request, requestId, controller }) => {
        const response = await handleRequest(
          request,
          requestId,
          this.handlersController.currentHandlers().filter(isHandlerKind("RequestHandler")),
          this.resolvedOptions,
          this.emitter,
          {
            onPassthroughResponse(request2) {
              const acceptHeader = request2.headers.get("accept");
              if (acceptHeader) {
                const nextAcceptHeader = acceptHeader.replace(
                  /(,\s+)?msw\/passthrough/,
                  ""
                );
                if (nextAcceptHeader) {
                  request2.headers.set("accept", nextAcceptHeader);
                } else {
                  request2.headers.delete("accept");
                }
              }
            }
          }
        );
        if (response) {
          controller.respondWith(response);
        }
        return;
      }

[90m15:44:12:803[0m [34m[websocket:on][0m adding "connection" event listener: async (connection) => {
    const handlers = options.getHandlers().filter(isHandlerKind("EventHandler"));
    if (handlers.length > 0) {
      options?.onMockedConnection(connection);
      await Promise.all(
        handlers.map((handler) => {
          return handler.run(connection);
        })
      );
      return;
    }
    const request = new Request(connection.client.url, {
      headers: {
        upgrade: "websocket",
        connection: "upgrade"
      }
    });
    await onUnhandledRequest(
      request,
      options.getUnhandledRequestStrategy()
    ).catch((error) => {
      const errorEvent = new Event("error");
      Object.defineProperty(errorEvent, "cause", {
        enumerable: true,
        configurable: false,
        value: error
      });
      connection.client.socket.dispatchEvent(errorEvent);
    });
    options?.onPassthroughConnection(connection);
    connection.server.connect();
  }

    ).catch((error) => {
      const errorEvent = new Event("error");
      Object.defineProperty(errorEvent, "cause", {
        enumerable: true,
        configurable: false,
        value: error
      });
      connection.client.socket.dispatchEvent(errorEvent);
    });
    options?.onPassthroughConnection(connection);
    connection.server.connect();
  }

[90m15:44:13:849[0m [34m[websocket:on][0m adding "connection" event listener: async (connection) => {
    const handlers = options.getHandlers().filter(isHandlerKind("EventHandler"));
    if (handlers.length > 0) {
      options?.onMockedConnection(connection);
      await Promise.all(
        handlers.map((handler) => {
          return handler.run(connection);
        })
      );
      return;
    }
    const request = new Request(connection.client.url, {
      headers: {
        upgrade: "websocket",
        connection: "upgrade"
      }
    });
    await onUnhandledRequest(
      request,
      options.getUnhandledRequestStrategy()
    ).catch((error) => {
      const errorEvent = new Event("error");
      Object.defineProperty(errorEvent, "cause", {
        enumerable: true,
        configurable: false,
        value: error
      });
      connection.client.socket.dispatchEvent(errorEvent);
    });
    options?.onPassthroughConnection(connection);
    connection.server.connect();
  }

          request,

                } else {
                  request2.headers.delete("accept");
                }
              }
            }
          }
        );
        if (response) {
          controller.respondWith(response);
        }
        return;
      }

[90m15:44:14:203[0m [34m[websocket:on][0m adding "connection" event listener: async (connection) => {
    const handlers = options.getHandlers().filter(isHandlerKind("EventHandler"));
    if (handlers.length > 0) {
      options?.onMockedConnection(connection);
      await Promise.all(
        handlers.map((handler) => {
          return handler.run(connection);
        })
      );
      return;
    }
    const request = new Request(connection.client.url, {
      headers: {
        upgrade: "websocket",
        connection: "upgrade"
      }
    });
    await onUnhandledRequest(
      request,
      options.getUnhandledRequestStrategy()
    ).catch((error) => {
      const errorEvent = new Event("error");
      Object.defineProperty(errorEvent, "cause", {
        enumerable: true,
        configurable: false,
        value: error
      });
      connection.client.socket.dispatchEvent(errorEvent);
    });
    options?.onPassthroughConnection(connection);
    connection.server.connect();
  }

      await Promise.all(
        handlers.map((handler) => {
          return handler.run(connection);
        })
      );
      return;
    }
    const request = new Request(connection.client.url, {
      headers: {
        upgrade: "websocket",
        connection: "upgrade"
      }
    });
    await onUnhandledRequest(
      request,
      options.getUnhandledRequestStrategy()
    ).catch((error) => {
      const errorEvent = new Event("error");
      Object.defineProperty(errorEvent, "cause", {
        enumerable: true,
        configurable: false,
        value: error
      });
      connection.client.socket.dispatchEvent(errorEvent);
    });
    options?.onPassthroughConnection(connection);
    connection.server.connect();
  }

          request,
          requestId,
          this.handlersController.currentHandlers().filter(isHandlerKind("RequestHandler")),
          this.resolvedOptions,
          this.emitter,
          {
            onPassthroughResponse(request2) {
              const acceptHeader = request2.headers.get("accept");
              if (acceptHeader) {
                const nextAcceptHeader = acceptHeader.replace(
                  /(,\s+)?msw\/passthrough/,
                  ""
                );
                if (nextAcceptHeader) {

                } else {
                  request2.headers.delete("accept");
                }
              }
            }
          }
        );
        if (response) {
          controller.respondWith(response);
        }
        return;
      }

[90m15:44:15:516[0m [34m[websocket:on][0m adding "connection" event listener: async (connection) => {
    const handlers = options.getHandlers().filter(isHandlerKind("EventHandler"));
    if (handlers.length > 0) {
      options?.onMockedConnection(connection);
      await Promise.all(
        handlers.map((handler) => {
          return handler.run(connection);
        })
      );
      return;
    }
    const request = new Request(connection.client.url, {
      headers: {
        upgrade: "websocket",
        connection: "upgrade"
      }
    });
    await onUnhandledRequest(
      request,
      options.getUnhandledRequestStrategy()
    ).catch((error) => {
      const errorEvent = new Event("error");
      Object.defineProperty(errorEvent, "cause", {
        enumerable: true,
        configurable: false,
        value: error
      });
      connection.client.socket.dispatchEvent(errorEvent);
    });
    options?.onPassthroughConnection(connection);
    connection.server.connect();
  }

          request,

          this.resolvedOptions,
          this.emitter,
          {
            onPassthroughResponse(request2) {

                } else {
                  request2.headers.delete("accept");
                }
              }
            }
          }
        );
        if (response) {
          controller.respondWith(response);
        }
        return;
      }

[90m15:44:15:632[0m [34m[websocket:on][0m adding "connection" event listener: async (connection) => {
    const handlers = options.getHandlers().filter(isHandlerKind("EventHandler"));
    if (handlers.length > 0) {
      options?.onMockedConnection(connection);
      await Promise.all(
        handlers.map((handler) => {
          return handler.run(connection);
        })
      );
      return;
    }
    const request = new Request(connection.client.url, {
      headers: {
        upgrade: "websocket",
        connection: "upgrade"
      }
    });
    await onUnhandledRequest(
      request,
      options.getUnhandledRequestStrategy()
    ).catch((error) => {
      const errorEvent = new Event("error");
      Object.defineProperty(errorEvent, "cause", {
        enumerable: true,
        configurable: false,
        value: error
      });
      connection.client.socket.dispatchEvent(errorEvent);
    });
    options?.onPassthroughConnection(connection);
    connection.server.connect();
  }

[90m15:44:16:136[0m [34m[websocket:on][0m adding "connection" event listener: async (connection) => {
    const handlers = options.getHandlers().filter(isHandlerKind("EventHandler"));
    if (handlers.length > 0) {
      options?.onMockedConnection(connection);
      await Promise.all(
        handlers.map((handler) => {
          return handler.run(connection);
        })
      );
      return;
    }
    const request = new Request(connection.client.url, {
      headers: {
        upgrade: "websocket",
        connection: "upgrade"
      }
    });
    await onUnhandledRequest(
      request,
      options.getUnhandledRequestStrategy()
    ).catch((error) => {
      const errorEvent = new Event("error");
      Object.defineProperty(errorEvent, "cause", {
        enumerable: true,
        configurable: false,
        value: error
      });
      connection.client.socket.dispatchEvent(errorEvent);
    });
    options?.onPassthroughConnection(connection);
    connection.server.connect();
  }

[90m15:44:16:928[0m [34m[websocket:on][0m adding "connection" event listener: async (connection) => {

    if (handlers.length > 0) {
      options?.onMockedConnection(connection);
      await Promise.all(
        handlers.map((handler) => {
          return handler.run(connection);
        })
      );
      return;
    }
    const request = new Request(connection.client.url, {
      headers: {
        upgrade: "websocket",
        connection: "upgrade"
      }
    });
    await onUnhandledRequest(
      request,
      options.getUnhandledRequestStrategy()
    ).catch((error) => {
      const errorEvent = new Event("error");
      Object.defineProperty(errorEvent, "cause", {
        enumerable: true,
        configurable: false,
        value: error
      });
      connection.client.socket.dispatchEvent(errorEvent);
    });
    options?.onPassthroughConnection(connection);
    connection.server.connect();
  }

[90m15:44:17:403[0m [34m[client-request-interceptor:on][0m adding "request" event listener: async ({ request, requestId, controller }) => {
        const response = await handleRequest(
          request,
          requestId,
          this.handlersController.currentHandlers().filter(isHandlerKind("RequestHandler")),
          this.resolvedOptions,
          this.emitter,
          {
            onPassthroughResponse(request2) {
              const acceptHeader = request2.headers.get("accept");
              if (acceptHeader) {
                const nextAcceptHeader = acceptHeader.replace(
                  /(,\s+)?msw\/passthrough/,
                  ""
                );
                if (nextAcceptHeader) {
                  request2.headers.set("accept", nextAcceptHeader);
                } else {
                  request2.headers.delete("accept");
                }
              }
            }
          }
        );
        if (response) {
          controller.respondWith(response);
        }
        return;
      }

[90m15:44:17:404[0m [34m[websocket:on][0m adding "connection" event listener: async (connection) => {
    const handlers = options.getHandlers().filter(isHandlerKind("EventHandler"));
    if (handlers.length > 0) {
      options?.onMockedConnection(connection);
      await Promise.all(
        handlers.map((handler) => {
          return handler.run(connection);
        })
      );
      return;
    }
    const request = new Request(connection.client.url, {
      headers: {
        upgrade: "websocket",
        connection: "upgrade"
      }
    });
    await onUnhandledRequest(
      request,
      options.getUnhandledRequestStrategy()
    ).catch((error) => {
      const errorEvent = new Event("error");
      Object.defineProperty(errorEvent, "cause", {
        enumerable: true,
        configurable: false,
        value: error
      });
      connection.client.socket.dispatchEvent(errorEvent);
    });
    options?.onPassthroughConnection(connection);
    connection.server.connect();
  }

    if (handlers.length > 0) {
      options?.onMockedConnection(connection);
      await Promise.all(
        handlers.map((handler) => {
          return handler.run(connection);
        })
      );
      return;
    }
    const request = new Request(connection.client.url, {
      headers: {
        upgrade: "websocket",
        connection: "upgrade"
      }
    });
    await onUnhandledRequest(
      request,
      options.getUnhandledRequestStrategy()
    ).catch((error) => {
      const errorEvent = new Event("error");
      Object.defineProperty(errorEvent, "cause", {
        enumerable: true,
        configurable: false,
        value: error
      });
      connection.client.socket.dispatchEvent(errorEvent);
    });
    options?.onPassthroughConnection(connection);
    connection.server.connect();
  }

[90m15:44:17:676[0m [34m[client-request-interceptor:on][0m adding "request" event listener: async ({ request, requestId, controller }) => {
        const response = await handleRequest(
          request,
          requestId,
          this.handlersController.currentHandlers().filter(isHandlerKind("RequestHandler")),
          this.resolvedOptions,
          this.emitter,
          {
            onPassthroughResponse(request2) {
              const acceptHeader = request2.headers.get("accept");
              if (acceptHeader) {
                const nextAcceptHeader = acceptHeader.replace(
                  /(,\s+)?msw\/passthrough/,
                  ""
                );
                if (nextAcceptHeader) {
                  request2.headers.set("accept", nextAcceptHeader);
                } else {
                  request2.headers.delete("accept");
                }
              }
            }
          }
        );
        if (response) {
          controller.respondWith(response);
        }
        return;
      }

[90m15:44:17:677[0m [34m[websocket:on][0m adding "connection" event listener: async (connection) => {
    const handlers = options.getHandlers().filter(isHandlerKind("EventHandler"));
    if (handlers.length > 0) {
      options?.onMockedConnection(connection);
      await Promise.all(
        handlers.map((handler) => {
          return handler.run(connection);
        })
      );
      return;
    }
    const request = new Request(connection.client.url, {
      headers: {
        upgrade: "websocket",
        connection: "upgrade"
      }
    });
    await onUnhandledRequest(
      request,
      options.getUnhandledRequestStrategy()
    ).catch((error) => {
      const errorEvent = new Event("error");
      Object.defineProperty(errorEvent, "cause", {
        enumerable: true,
        configurable: false,
        value: error
      });
      connection.client.socket.dispatchEvent(errorEvent);
    });
    options?.onPassthroughConnection(connection);
    connection.server.connect();
  }

[90m15:44:17:907[0m [34m[websocket:on][0m adding "connection" event listener: async (connection) => {
    const handlers = options.getHandlers().filter(isHandlerKind("EventHandler"));
    if (handlers.length > 0) {
      options?.onMockedConnection(connection);
      await Promise.all(
        handlers.map((handler) => {
          return handler.run(connection);
        })
      );
      return;
    }
    const request = new Request(connection.client.url, {
      headers: {
        upgrade: "websocket",
        connection: "upgrade"
      }
    });
    await onUnhandledRequest(
      request,
      options.getUnhandledRequestStrategy()
    ).catch((error) => {
      const errorEvent = new Event("error");
      Object.defineProperty(errorEvent, "cause", {
        enumerable: true,
        configurable: false,
        value: error
      });
      connection.client.socket.dispatchEvent(errorEvent);
    });
    options?.onPassthroughConnection(connection);
    connection.server.connect();
  }

[90m15:44:18:293[0m [34m[client-request-interceptor:on][0m adding "request" event listener: async ({ request, requestId, controller }) => {
        const response = await handleRequest(
          request,
          requestId,
          this.handlersController.currentHandlers().filter(isHandlerKind("RequestHandler")),
          this.resolvedOptions,
          this.emitter,
          {
            onPassthroughResponse(request2) {
              const acceptHeader = request2.headers.get("accept");
              if (acceptHeader) {
                const nextAcceptHeader = acceptHeader.replace(
                  /(,\s+)?msw\/passthrough/,
                  ""
                );
                if (nextAcceptHeader) {
                  request2.headers.set("accept", nextAcceptHeader);
                } else {
                  request2.headers.delete("accept");
                }
              }
            }
          }
        );
        if (response) {
          controller.respondWith(response);
        }
        return;
      }

          request,
          requestId,
          this.handlersController.currentHandlers().filter(isHandlerKind("RequestHandler")),
          this.resolvedOptions,
          this.emitter,
          {
            onPassthroughResponse(request2) {
              const acceptHeader = request2.headers.get("accept");
              if (acceptHeader) {
                const nextAcceptHeader = acceptHeader.replace(
                  /(,\s+)?msw\/passthrough/,
                  ""
                );
                if (nextAcceptHeader) {
                  request2.headers.set("accept", nextAcceptHeader);
                } else {
                  request2.headers.delete("accept");
                }
              }
            }
          }
        );
        if (response) {
          controller.respondWith(response);
        }
        return;
      }

[90m15:44:18:609[0m [34m[websocket:on][0m adding "connection" event listener: async (connection) => {
    const handlers = options.getHandlers().filter(isHandlerKind("EventHandler"));
    if (handlers.length > 0) {
      options?.onMockedConnection(connection);
      await Promise.all(
        handlers.map((handler) => {
          return handler.run(connection);
        })
      );
      return;
    }
    const request = new Request(connection.client.url, {
      headers: {
        upgrade: "websocket",
        connection: "upgrade"
      }
    });
    await onUnhandledRequest(
      request,
      options.getUnhandledRequestStrategy()
    ).catch((error) => {
      const errorEvent = new Event("error");
      Object.defineProperty(errorEvent, "cause", {
        enumerable: true,
        configurable: false,
        value: error
      });
      connection.client.socket.dispatchEvent(errorEvent);
    });
    options?.onPassthroughConnection(connection);
    connection.server.connect();
  }
